Author: Rain1601 <rain97@vip.qq.com>
Date:   Tue May 26 23:22:17 2026 +0800

    fix(artifacts): strip meta-narration preamble before first # heading
    
    DeepSeek-chat and similar models reliably prepend 2-5 lines of
    meta-narration to markdown deliverables ("先拉取数据..." / "现在直接
    写出最终交付物，不含任何过程性文字") despite explicit prompt rules
    (guardrails §5a) forbidding it. Three iterations of strengthening
    the prompt across 2026-05-26 hit diminishing returns — the model
    quotes the rule back while violating it in the same paragraph.
    
    This is the deterministic fix at the seam: LocalFileArtifactStore.
    write() now calls _strip_preamble() on kind=markdown writes.
    
    Behavior:
    - Content already starting with "# ": untouched
    - Content with "# " heading later (newline-anchored OR inline-
      squashed onto preamble's line — run 4 observed mode): strip
      everything before the first "# "
    - Subheaders only (## etc.) without a top-level #: untouched
    - No # at all: untouched (raw failure surfaces to reviewer rather
      than getting silently empty file)
    
    Match rule uses [^#]# (non-# char immediately before "# ") so
    "##"/"###"/etc subheaders don't false-trigger. Logs stripped
    line/byte count on every actual strip.
    
    Verification across runs:
    - Run 6 (just-after-deploy): final-research.md opens with
      "# 中国半导体设备板块" on line 1 — preamble gone
    - Tests: 11 cases including all observed failure modes (newline-
      anchored, inline-squashed, phantom ## + real #, edge cases)
    
    Caveat documented in tests: aggressive enough to false-strip if
    a research note legitimately has "# " mid-line. Acceptable —
    research markdown convention is heading-per-line.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

